ENUGU – Women Empowerment Education and Peace Building Initiative (WEPBI) has emphasized the need to support more political participation of women in politics. The call was made during a day Roundtable meeting for Media practitioners in Enugu State on their roles in creating visibility for female political aspirants in the state organized by WEPBI in collaboration with Global Affairs Canada and ActionAid Nigeria held at Predia hotel Enugu. Speaking at the event, the Executive Director of Women Empowerment and Peace Building initiative (WEPBI), Mrs Miriam Menkiti said ”we envision a society where women will have their pride of place in politics to achieve gender equality and democratic. “Any woman is capable of making a change so we should be given the opportunity and support to contest for election “We have great women in our country that can lead and perform very well but unfortunately they are not given the opportunity to contest,”. She lamented the way and manner women politicians are subjected to gender-related violence “this is wrong because this attitude is being used to scare women away from politics”. POLL “Women should be given the opportunity to participate in politics and help tackle gender-related issues and other issues for a change of system in our country Menkiti advocated for a bill that will provide special seats for women in the National Assembly She thereby enjoined media practitioners to give adequate coverage to women’s issues, especially political issues. She also advised women to engage in grassroots politics and network with other politicians in order to enjoy a successful career in politics.